the delegation, led by vadim m. malyshev, chairman of the soviet state committee on supervision of nuclear power safety, was given a tour wednesday of hinkley point station near combwich in somerset, in southwest england
malyshev told reporters monday the soviet union is designing new nuclear reactors since the april 1986 disaster at the chernobyl plant in the ukraine, which killed 31 people and sent radiation drifting over europe
