a heavy snow warning was issued for the eastern foothills of northern colorado through tonight. snow advisories also were posted in nebraska's southern panhandle. in addition, forecasters issued winter storm watches for parts of wyoming and kansas
today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms from the southern plains across the lower mississippi valley, alabama, the tennessee and lower ohio valleys and the southern appalachians; rain from oklahoma and eastern texas into kentucky and tennessee; snow from northern arizona and the central rockies into the central high plains; windy conditions from southern california into western texas
highs will be in the 50s or 60s in much of the nation; below freezing over parts of colorado and southeast wyoming; 30s and 40s from the northern and central rockies across the northern plains into the upper great lakes region; 70s and low 80s over california, the desert southwest and from southern and eastern texas to the southern atlantic coast
