a casket empty except for a dress, a rose and other remembrances was interred during a brief ceremony attended by a dozen mourners of denise naslund, allegedly murdered by killer ted bundy 14 years ago
the 20-minute memorial on wednesday was as close as denise's mother, eleanor rose, could get to the realization of a longtime wish that her 18-year-old daughter be buried
fragments of denise's bones were found strewn in the wooded cascade foothills east of seattle in the summer of 1974. king county authorities, who kept the remains as part of their investigation of bundy, lost them years ago
looking on through tears, ms. rose watched wednesday as a pink casket, containing only her daughter's favorite dress, a silk rose, a crucifix and some photographs and letters, was buried at a cemetery on a west seattle hillside
