crews worked through the night to right the 22 freight cars and five locomotives derailed in the wednesday evening wreck
two firefighters and a police officer were treated for smoke inhalation at flagstaff regional medical center and released, officials said
the eastbound santa fe trains collided when one failed to slow for the other at a point where parallel tracks cross, said state corporation commission spokesman jon poston
a fireball erupted from one of the diesel locomotive, then the fire spread to other engines, said police sgt. pasqual macias
some of those engines were embedded into the ground, and they were strewn all over _ some right side up, some perpendicular to the track,'' said fire department capt. paul hellenberg. some of the locomotives went down a 20-foot embankment, hellenberg said
the evacuation of homes and businesses on the east side was called off about two hours later because shipping manifests showed there was no hazardous material near the fire
one car was loaded with explosives and another contained a flammable liquid or gas, but neither derailed, said hellenberg
two streets were closed, but they reopened after the fire was put out
