iraq said today it would stop missile attacks on iranian cities for three days beginning at midnight, then said it fired three missiles into iran 10 hours before the truce was to begin
in another development, an iranian warship today attacked and set ablaze a cypriot supertanker in the southern persian gulf. the tanker's crew of 45 was rescued by salvage tugboats after the tanker ran aground
also today, the u.s. navy said two anti-aircraft missiles that may be soviet-made sam-7s were found aboard an iranian gunboat the navy discovered abandoned and drifting at the southern end of the gulf
the official iraqi news agency, monitored in nicosia, said one of the three iraqi long-range missiles fired at iran hit qom, seat of iran's religious hierarchy, and two hit isfahan, capital of the ancient persian empire
it said the missiles were fired about 2 p.m. local time, 10 hours before the proposed cease-fire was to begin
iran had no immediate reaction to the missile attacks on isfahan, in western iran, and qom, 100 miles south of tehran
but an iranian embassy official in ankara, turkey, was quoted as saying today that iran will comply with the proposed cease-fire if iraq does
iranian attacks will automatically come to an end if iraq stops the war of the cities,'' embassy spokesman riza bagri was quoted as saying by the semi-official anatolia news agency
hundreds of civilians have been killed in the missile duel during which iraq fired 105 missiles into tehran, 13 into qom and 10 into isfahan since feb. 29. iran says it fired 45 missiles into baghdad, a city of 5 million people, and dozens into the northern city of mosul and other cities in iraq
the iraqi news agency today quoted an unidentified government spokesman as saying the cease-fire was ``a gesture of courtesy'' to turkish prime minister turgut ozal, who was scheduled to begin a 48-hour visit to iraq on friday
ozal was on an official visit to tehran on feb. 29, and one of the first iraqi missiles fired into tehran crashed near a downtown hotel where members of the turkish delegation were staying. none of the turkish officials was hurt
