the lebanese opened fire on a syrian patrol that entered the eastern edge of the christians' 300-square-mile enclave in northeast lebanon before dawn, one source said
the source, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the two sides clashed for about 30 minutes with automatic weapons and grenades near the village of zighrine. no lebanese casualties were reported
zighrine, a christian village, lies 15 miles northeast of beirut
the source said the syrian patrol ``withdrew from the zighrine area after the clash.'' he did not elaborate
syria, the main power broker in lebanon, maintains 25,000 troops in eastern and northern provinces under a 1976 arab league peacekeeping mandate
