park workers converted the crosses at both conservatories into pillars of flowers climbing almost to the ceiling, she said
my concern is that the cross put up by a public body on public property was a violation of the first amendment,'' said jane whicher, staff counsel for the aclu in illinois. ``it shouldn't have been erected in the first place, but i commend the park district on removing it so quickly.''
