the city committee had asked national leaders to reconsider the annexation demand in february after the communist party central committee said nagorno-karabakh belongs to azerbaijan. the presidium of the supreme soviet, the national parliament, approved a package of cultural and economic improvements for the region on march 23 but did not address the territorial issue
street demonstrations and strikes in nagorno-karabakh and armenia's capital, yerevan, have tested soviet leader mikhail s. gorbachev's policy of glasnost, or openness. at least 32 people were killed in ethnic violence in sumgait in azerbaijan last month
