we will continue to act against the violence until we stamp it out,'' shamir, leader of the right-wing likud bloc, told hundreds of cheering jewish settlers during a tour of herodion, 5 miles south of bethlehem
in the west bank town of ramallah, israeli troops sealed off the city hall after reports of a bomb threat, arab witnesses said
secretary of state george p. shultz defended his recent meeting with arab-americans who belong to the palestine liberation organization's parliament-in-exile. benjamin netanyahu, israel's ambassador to the united nations, said he was resigning immediately, a few weeks earlier than he originally planned, to speak out against the meeting
on wednesday, when palestinians observed land day, israel clamped down on palestinians in the west bank and gaza strip with its toughest restrictions in 20 years of occupation
land day commemorates a confrontation on march 30, 1976, when israeli arabs protested the forced sale of 1,600 acres of their land for jewish settlement. six arabs were killed
the army barred reporters from entering the west bank and gaza strip except in news pools with an army escort, and restricted the movement of palestinians
the measures, however, failed to prevent violence. officials said four arabs were shot and killed and 39 were wounded by gunfire wednesday, and two were injured in gaza
israel radio said today the interior ministry placed new travel restrictions on palestinians from east jerusalem, where 130,000 arabs live. israel annexed the predominantly arab sector of the city in 1967
it said palestinians aged 16 to 35 now need special permits to travel to jordan, and these will be issued only if the request is for a stay of at least nine months. the object is to stop the plo from sending couriers into the occupied territories
in ramallah, chamber of commerce head hadar kasis told a reporter the military authorities informed him palestinians could withdraw only $1,000 a month from bank accounts
earlier restrictions bar arabs from bringing more than $1,200 at a time across the bridges from jordan. the moves are designed to keep the plo from compensating merchants and workers for loss of income during anti-israeli strikes and protests
we are prepared for anything. ... we can exist just on bread and zatar (a peppery spice),'' said kasis, a gift-store owner
the israeli army said it received reports of an explosion in the ramallah city hall area about midday today, and arab witnesses said soldiers briefly sealed off the area
the witnesses said israeli or municipal officials apparently had received a bomb threat, but the details were sketchy. israel sealed off the west bank to media monday night and the movements of journalists were severely limited
the israeli-appointed acting mayor, ahmed assayad, said there was an unsuccessful attempt late wednesday to break into the building. he said he left city hall about 11 a.m. (4 a.m. est) and knew of no attack
underground leaflets signed by the plo have ordered all arab municipal councils to resign, accusing them of collaborating with israeli authorities
in remarks broadcast today by israel radio, shultz reacted to israeli protests over his meeting last saturday with edward said and ibrahim abu lughud. he said it was ``beyond the pale'' to suggest he could not meet american citizens
shultz also stressed the importance of finding palestinian negotiators: ``palestinians are part of the peace issue. we have got to find a way to be in contact with them.''
