extra officers were called to the talladega federal correctional institute to quell an hour-long disturbance involving cuban prisoners, a spokeswoman said today
no injuries were reported in the wednesday incident, but guards had to use a tear gas-like chemcial agent on four detainees who resisted officers, said karen stephens
at no time was the security or safety of the facility in danger,'' she said. ms. stephens said it was unclear what prompted the disturbance
brian ross, another spokesman for the facility, said the disturbance was confined to one cell block holding 16 cubans. he said they made a lot of noise and covered the front of the block so they could not be seen or counted
the talladega prison holds 167 cuban detainees, some of whom were transferred to the facility following uprisings at federal prisons in atlanta and oakdale, la., late last year
