the presidential spokesman said meese was at the white house today for a ``security meeting'' on an undisclosed subject
the president was involved in the meeting,'' he said, but ``there were no private discussions between the two either before or after the meeting and none are planned.''
meese is the target of a broadening criminal investigation. department sources have said the top officials quit because they felt meese's legal problems were ``poisoning'' the justice department
on wednesday, sen. bob packwood, r-ore., said flatly that meese should resign. senate democratic leader robert byrd also called for his resignation, calling him ``the crown jewel of the sleaze factor in reagan administration history.''
