sears, roebuck &amp; co. has filed with the state to charter a second bank in delaware
sears, which already owns greenwood trust co., has filed an application to open a credit card bank called discover card bank of new castle, susan l. winters, acting deputy bank commissioner, said wednesday
the filing comes under that part of delaware law that pertains to any new bank being established in the state. a hearing is set for may 2 on the application
sears issues its discover credit card through greenwood trust, which it acquired in 1985
ms. winters said sears plans to transfer some of greenwood trust's credit card acounts to the new bank if it is approved
under federal banking laws, the growth of non-banks, which includes greenwood trust, are restricted. ms. winter said the new bank's ability to grow would not be restricted
when the federal law restricting the growth of non-banks was filed, ``sears made a commitment to look for ways to continue to make credit card loans,'' said paul marrone for dean witter reynolds, the sears subsidiary that oversees discover card operations
the application we have filed is a first step in the development of that commitment,'' marrone said
in what is being billed as one of the largest non-government issues in history, $1.45 billion in bonds have been sold to help kohlberg kravis roberts &amp; co. pay off bank loans from its buyout of jim walter corp
kohlberg kravis took jim walters private last year for about $2.4 billion, about $2 billion of which was financed by bank loans. since then the new york-based investment firm has been selling selected jim walter's assets to help finance the deal
jim walter, which has its headquarters in tampa, fla., is a diversified building materials and natural resources company that operates primarily in the south and southwest. it also is one of the country's largest home builders, specializing in inexpensive, partially finished ``shell'' houses
walter had 74,000 single-family mortgages in 22 states totaling $1.74 billion that were packaged together to back the bond issue
kkr realized they had a very unusual asset in these mortgages,'' said peter hoey, senior vice president of financial security assurance
hoey said the bond issue was ``totally sold out to a blue-chip list'' comprised of large pension funds, life insurance companies and banks from around the world
the mortgages were sold to a special trust and used to back the bond issue, which financial security guaranteed with a triple-a rating
homeowners pay their morgtages into the trust, which has a cushion to protect against any defaults by homeowners. that cash flow will pay the interest on the bonds, which were sold in five different maturities, each carrying a different interest rate
the purpose was not to take weak credit and make it triple-a and take on risk, but to take complex and unusual collateral that the marketplace has difficulty understanding'' and package it to sell, hoey said
the average buyer of a jim walter home requires a low-cost mortgage and therefore is not a typical homebuyer
jim walter does not provide the land on which its houses are built, which cuts down on the price of the homes. in addition, the company leaves its houses as much as 30 percent incomplete, making them affordable to blue-collar, first-time homebuyers, hoey said
kohlberg kravis has spearheaded a number of major leveraged buyouts, including the $6.2 billion buyout of beatrice cos. the company said this week that it is seeking permission to acquire up to 15 percent of texaco inc. report are for week ended tuesday. all other figures are for the week ended wednesday.</note>
assets of the nation's 420 money market mutual funds fell $548.4 million in the latest week, the investment company institute said thursday
the decline, to $278.23 billion in the seven-day period ended wednesday, followed a $730.3 million drop in the funds' assets the previous week, according to the washington-based mutual fund trade group
the funds' assets hit a record high $280.02 billion in the week ended feb. 24
the investment company institute said that in the latest week, assets of 210 general purpose funds rose $624.5 million to $82.86 billion, assets of 98 broker-dealer funds dropped $620.2 million to $117.04 billion, and assets of 112 institutional funds declined $552.7 million to $78.33 billion
the seven-day average yield on money market mutual funds was unchanged in the week ended tuesday at 6.04 percent, according to donoghue's money fund report, a trade journal based in holliston, mass
the 30-day average yield fell to 6.05 percent from 6.07 percent the previous week, donoghue's said
the average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 43 days, down from 44 days, donoghue's said
separately, the newsletter bank rate monitor said its survey of 100 leading commercial banks, savings and loan assocations and savings banks in the nation's 10 largest markets showed the effective annual yield available on money market accounts was unchanged from a week earlier at 5.70 percent as of wednesday
the north palm beach, fla.-based newsletter said the effective annual yield available on special savings accounts, called super now accounts, was also unchanged, at 5.15 percent
bank rate monitor said the effective annual yield was 6.78 percent on six-month certificates of deposit, down from 6.79 the previous week. yields were 7.12 percent on 1-year cds, unchanged; 7.53 percent on 2{-year cds, up from 7.52 percent; and 7.99 percent on 5-year cds, unchanged
fremont general corp. said thursday it has agreed to sell all of its property and casualty insurance operations to a management-led group for $82 million in cash, notes and stock warrants
the operations are being acquired by a new company formed by managers of a fremont general subsidiary, fremont insurance co
being sold are fremont indemnity co., fremont comspensation insurance co., fremont reinsurance co. and comstock insurance co. the latter two operations were discontinued last year, and fremont general sought unsuccessfully to spin off the first two to shareholders
upon completion of the deal, fremont general will remain a financial services concern with commercial and life insurance operations, a real estate finance unit and half ownership of a workers compensation insurance firm. it also is awaiting regulatory approval to acquire malibu savings &amp; loan association
under terms of the deal announced thursday, fremont general will receive $20 million in cash, a 90-day note for $5 million, preferred stock with warrants to purchase 9.9 percent of the buyer's outstanding shares valued at $35 million, and a 10-year zero-coupon note valued at $22 million
blue chips led stock prices higher near the close today in an atmosphere of caution heading into the long easter-passover weekend
five minutes before the close, the dow jones average of 30 industrials was up 11.27 at 1,989.39
stock prices edged upward near the close of a quiet session today in an atmosphere of caution heading into the long easter-passover weekend
analysts said traders were reluctant to carry big positions through the weekend, especially with a labor department report due out friday on the employment situation for march
both the stock and bond markets will be closed on friday, and thus will not have a chance to respond to any surprises in the employment data until monday
in the last monthly set of figures, a much stronger-than-expected increase in nonfarm payroll employment dealt the bond market a sharp setback
brokers said money managers at investing institutions had pretty much completed maneuvers to ready their portfolios for reports to clients on their performance in the first quarter, which ended with today's trading
the dow jones average of 30 industrials rose 9.94 to 1,988.06, finishing the week with a gain of 9.11 points
for the first quarter of the year, the average chalked up a net gain of 49.23 points
advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 6 to 5 on the new york stock exchange, with 807 up, 676 down and 485 unchanged
